values: Alright, as I am getting bored with this lj, I *gasp* made a new one. I would however like to say that this is the longest I have kept a journal. WOO!! Goodbye dream_in_red, hello <lj user="felix_felicis_" />

Tag thingy.. This is hard cause I like alot of songs, so off the top of my head... (in no specific order)

1.More Than A Feeling--Boston

2.Thinking Over--Dana Glover

3.I'll Be--Edwin McCain

4.Hide and Seek--Imogen Heap

5.Behind These Hazel Eyes & Because of You--Kelly Clarkson (I know, I cheated a little on that but its the same artist)

6.Untitled--Simple Plan

7.World on Fire--Sarah McLachlan

 

And as I dont go to other peoples journals to read them, I have no "friends" so I wont name anybody.

Jasmine, I got your letter yesterday and I will be writing you back soon.

Amber Diane Fries's Aliases

Your movie star name: Yogurt Bruce
Your fashion designer name is Amber Paris
Your socialite name is French Fries New York
Your fly girl / guy name is A Fri
Your detective name is Dog Clarke County
Your barfly name is Yogurt Strawberry Daquiri
Your soap opera name is Diane
Your rock star name is Reeses Plane
Your star wars name is Ambreg Friorl
Your punk rock band name is The Bored Spork
The Amazing Meganame Generator
Dude!! A punk rock band named The Bored Spork!!!! That fuggin rocks! Of course, thats really the only cool answer about the whole meme, but that makes up for the whole thing.

We have finally moved into the apartment!! We were over here last night, but not everything got moved in until today, so we are officially moved out. We went shopping for groceries. Our kitchen looks pretty sad right now. But, oh well. Jesse started working on Wednesday so now I wont be paying for everything myself anymore. Whew.

I went and talked to SWCC the other day. Now I just have to sign up and start figuring out what classes I want to take. I'm kinda excited. I hope it comes through.

Oh. My. Fucking. Holy. Hell. I want to se GoF SOOOOOO ridiculously bad!!!!!!!!!!!! I just saw the trailer and GoF icons are starting to pop up everywhere. Looks wicked good. Why cant November come sooner. But, the 6th book comes out 2 days before my b-day, WOOT. Dude, I said wicked good. Weird.
I am such a horrible slut! Jasmine, I am soo sorry for not writing you back yet. *shame* I WILL do it though. Promise. I lub you :)

Got a new journal layout again. I like it. It's cute. Little kiddish but come on, I am little kiddish XD

MTV's new show Damage Control is really funny. You should watch it sometime. I like it. One of the best shows they've had.

I wanna see Sin City. Why? I dont know.

Hope you had a Happy Easter!! Mine was pretty damn good. Got home from work to the smell of chicken parmesan. Yes, I talked dad into making me chicken parm for easter. WOOT!

Wow. Long time no update. Not much to write about though. Why, oh why, is American Idol more popular than Nashville Star? I know its country but holy hell the people are SO MUCH more talented. Instead of always just choosing other peoples songs to sing, they have one show where they write their own song and perform it. This years AI finalists arent really doing anything for me.
Happy 19th Birthday Jasmine <lj user="moonlight_mandy" /> ! Love ya babe.
Alright, got AIM now. Whats your screen name?

HAHAHAHAHAHAHAHA!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! FINALLY! Internet on my laptop! And just for the occasion, I changed my email address, and will probably change my LJ (yet again) to slightly resemble my address. Sorry Jasmine. I know your getting sick of switching my shit over. I'm thinking weebs_wiggum. What do you think? AND, I have Yahoo! Messenger....do you have that? I am beyond excited to have internet on my comp. WOOT!

Its about damn time this week has ended. Working 7 days straight sucks my ass. Also, I have a new thing to do at work. I cook breakfast on Tues and Wed (which is why my days off are now Thurs and Fri). But, its actual breakfast.. pancakes, eggs, bacon, hashbrowns, country fried steak, steak... that stuff. Which means I have to be there at 6 in the morning!! But its cool, I wish all my days were 6-2 instead of 8-4. ANNNNND we get highspeed on Friday, WOOHOO!!!!! *is way to excited to be normal*

WOOT! Got a laptop yesterday!! Its really pretty. But, I cant get online :( We're gonna try and get highspeed and if we end up doing that it could be 1-2 weeks before I can get online on my comp. That makes me sad. But, I got a laptop *bounces in excitement*

Bad Robot night!!!! WOOT! 7 cant come fast enough. Is it healthy to be this pumped about tv shows? Probably not...but oh well :)

We had slop last night. Mom really does not enjoy me calling it that. She prefers Dad calling it goo. But, I'm right in calling it slop. Its basically shephards pie...mashed potatoes, green beans, peas, tomatoes, corn, hamb. meat all thrown together and it looks like slop that you would feed a pig, but its really good.

We're supposed to go up to West Des Moines Sunday for a freezer and so I can get a laptop..but I'm not sure if its gonna happen or not. Dad said that we are for sure because its the only way he can get me off his back. Boo-Yah!!

Green Days Boulevard of Broken Dreams kicks so much ass. I love it.

sucks. Worked 15 hours on Sat. 8-11 and turned around and went to work the next morning at 7. But, I got today off WOO!!! And we're supposed to get more crap ass weather when the snow from last week isnt even gone and the dirt roads are still icy. I wanna live in Cali or Hawaii.
*Squeels like a schoolgirl* I've got a journal layout. Like a REAL one. With a header. Its so gorgemus. Look at it *Points and jabs at journal layout* Sooo pretty with the C/C. *Pets*

Two frickin days!! Since when does school let out for two days in a row?! Never! Thats when. And I think they are gonna get out tomorrow too. Supposedly there is supposed to be a snowstorm tonight, and its supposed to spit out like 6 inches. I never got that many days off in a row. And they just had winter vacation too. Yesterday was supposed to be their day back. *shakes head*

Freezing rain sucks my ass. Although, I didnt have to go into work today, YAY!!!!!!!!! It also makes for a good day to listen to new CDs. Jasmine, got your package today, LOVE it SOOO much, Thank you!! Charlie and Claire from Lost are my new OTP love. Just look at how cute they are in my icon (even though I'm sure that pic is a manip). But, I'm way freaked out that they are going to kill her off the show. If that happens I will be extremely PISSED OFF. Its amazing how the character changes how you veiw the actor. I Hated Emilie de Ravin with a passion because she was Tess on Roswell. When I saw she was on Lost I was like that bitch. But I absolutely LOVE her. Shes so sweet and adorable. And, in my opinion way prettier than she was on Roswell. Anyhoo.. Alias returns this Wed. after a new ep. of Lost. How awesome is that. Wednesday is now JJ Abrams Day in my book. ::Is way excited::

Wow... yet again I havent updated this journal in like..well, forever. And, to keep the tradition going, I sent your Christmas present late, Jasmine. I sent it to your college address because I wasnt sure how much longer you were gonna be at your house, if your even still there. But, its on its way!!

PoA=fantabulouslyamazinglywonderfullyawesome. 'Nuff said.

Went shopping for clothes for when I go out to Denver in two weeks. Word to the wise. Just because you see the cutest looking outfit and you want it really bad, check the price. I went into The Buckle and on a manaquin they had this Lucky hooded sweatshirt with an undershirt, a scarf and beanie and I was like I gotta have it...went to the checkout counter with that outfit a watch and perfume and dead serious about had a heart attack  when they told me the price. I dont think I will divulge how much it was because well, it was really bad. But I've got. 4 pairs of pants which all have to be sent to me because 2 of them are to long so they are being hemmed and the other 2 have to be sent from another store cause they didnt have my size. I also got some PJs and sweatpant type bottoms with a hoody and two pairs of the worlds softest socks. Next week we have to go again cuz I still need to get: two pairs of shoes (sneakers and dress-y type shoots--thats shoes and boots together, best of both worlds, a coat and some more long sleeve shirts/sweatshirts that arent from The Buckle :)

Jasmine...what do you want for Christmas? Before I'm broke man!:) J/K

I've been trying to decide whether or not I'm going to get PSP 7 or 8. I want to make icons, but its so damned expensive. 
Jasmine... I need your address. I have a little letter written, sealed and stamped, but nowhere to send it to! :)

Freaking monsters. So yucky and scary. I went to take a shower after I got off work tonight and as I'm pulling back the curtain to turn it on, a gigantic spider runs into the middle of the tub. I jumped like 100ft in the air and 50ft backwards dude. It was so big that when I turned on the faucet to send it down the drain, it fucking scrambled (quite successfully I might add) away from the drain. But I got the big bastard by throwing water from a cup at it at the same time. So, in the end he lost. HAHAHA!!! ::shivers:: I hate spiders.

Jasmine... I lub you. You are the second best friend I have had in my whole life, and the only person that I have met and then moved away from that I have kept in touch with. You are WAY to negative about yourself. You are extremely smart, funny, nice, caring, and the most adorable thing ever! Again, in short, I lub you.
I'm sorry I dont call you. It has ABSOLUTELY nothing to do with you. I should put forth more effort to call you up, and hopefully if I get moved to the day shift (cross your fingers) I will call you more. 


HA!!! I totally forgot about Mr. Fines... I mean Hines. Yes... good times.

My dad and stepmom came out to see me over the weekend. It was pretty fun. We stayed at the boat Fri., Sat., and Sun. night. I wasnt all to excited about it bc when they told me what we were doing I wasnt so enthused. We went down to Missouri Saturday to see my dads best friend. I remember we used to visit him and his wife alot when I was little but I hadnt seen them in 10 or so years. (Except for Spencer, I saw him at the wedding over Summer for a few days, but I never really talked to him. So I figured I'd be all left out and bored but it turned out to be pretty fun. However, I have decided that I DO NOT do horses. They are scary creatures. Tammy was shaving the horses legs and it went to bat at a fly and kicked her head, she had to get 6 stitches. Let me tell you, I stayed far away from them :) And then on Sunday we went up to Cedar Rapids to visit Kelli's sister that I barely know, so again, I figured I'd be left out, but that too was really fun. AND, I know all of them better so I no longer have to be awkward or mute around them like I was at the wedding :) All in all, good times were had.
When I was coming back home Mon. morning Lindsey and Briar were outside, and as I pull up Lindsey comes running up to the truck with a puppy in her arms. I wasnt going to get all excited bc I knew that my parents didnt want a dog since our landlord wont let it be inside, so I figured we were watching it for someone. But, ITS OURS BABY!!!!! She's so frickin cute! Her name is Reggie (my mom chose it) after Reggie White from the Packers. Apparently they tried to call me over the weekend to ask my input on the name, but my phone was turned off. The two names they were thinking of were Reggie and Sheba. I woulda said Reggie. Oh, its a German Shephard of course :) But a complete pain in the ass. She HATES to be outside alone so she whines and barks and it sounds like shes dying. She needs to get trained and fast.
I'm getting my glasses today ::does happy dance:: I havent had glasses in forever. They were like 265 bucks, but with my insurance its 91. I lurve insurance.

Where is it that these mysterious bruises come from? I mean, I'm pretty damn sure that if I hit my arm in the least bit, let alone hard enough to bruise it, I would FEEL it. I was brushing my hair the other day, and I noticed a rather large and nasty bruise on the inside of my arm and was like WTF?! Where did that come from? So, I have decided that I must beat myself while I am asleep. There is no other explanation. I'm dreaming that I'm Rocky or something and beat the shit out of myself. Yes, thats it.

::sigh:: I want to see PoA. I still HAVE NOT seen it. Pisses me off. They were supposed to bring it to out theater this summer but they never did. GRRRRR.......

I got a new TV. It fricken rocks. That is all.

Oh.. Jasmine, I just tonight got your voicemail that you left. But, with me not knowing when you called I dont know how long ago it was. I'm sorry. I didnt just blow you off though. Whats your #?

We went to the circus yesterday. It was a teeny-tiny ass circus, but it was something to do. Have you ever seen an elephant pee? Whoa. Then we went to Pizza Hut!!!! Breadsticks, WOOOOOO!!!!!!! Last Sunday I had just breadsticks for lunch. It was fantasmic. God, why am I such a loser?

So, YAY!! Since my dad isnt in Minnesota anymore he ordered some more parts for my car last night. He's gonna start to work on it again this weekend. We have like 4 or 5 more things that we need to order for  the interior and then we're done (with the interior)!!! I had saved up like 2 grand in my account, and then last night when he ordered some stuff... I almost died. It costed 1160 something. :( I hope he finishes it really soon. I wanna drive my pretty car.

Its frickin August so why is it so damn cold?!?! Its like in the 60's here. I want like the mid to high 70's.

Yeah so I cut the shit out of my thumb at work today. It hurt like hell. And it bled. Alot. Its still bleeding but not all that much. And it still hurts. 
We had a big ass storm last night. It woulda been cool if the worst of it hadnt decided to come while I was driving home from work. I couldnt see shit. My brother got into an accident Sunday. Hit a wall going 50 mph. He hydroplained or something like that. He's alright, sore, but alright. His truck is destroyed though. He's waiting for the insurance company to do the estimate. They dont even know whether the trucks fix-able or not. Figures. He has really bad luck. Getting arrested, truck got impounded, lost like 5 phones and now this. ::shakes head:: My whole family has bad luck.

Watching Bug Juice on Disney right now. Its weird to think that right now those kids are between the ages of 18-20. Maybe even older. Freaky. I remember watching it when it first came out, but it didnt seem that long ago. Thats a really cool camp. I wanna go there. A bit old, but I wanna go :) They should have done a second season with the same camp and kids. They should have like a reunion show. Now THAT would be freaky.

So, the other day at work, we had a water fight and it was quite entertaining. Uncomfortable as I was wet near the end, but still fun. And then tonight, I was standing beside the steam table throwing leftover peas and corn nowhere in particular when Kathleen (the lead buffet cook) walks up and stands like 3 feet behind me puting food onto speedracks when I decided to be annoying and throw a pea at her over my shoulder without looking. Well, she starts to kinda sorta freak, by saying OH my GOD over and over. So, finally I turn around and she points to her ear. I threw the freakin pea in her ear!!!!!!!! It was hilarious. I couldnt stop laughing and all she could say was "Oh my god!" It was quite amusing if I do say so myself.

Saw King Arthur tonight. Wow. It was friggen awesome. Clive Owen (Arthur) ::wipes drool off chin:: is SOO hot. That has to be the first KA movie that I have seen that I actually wanted Guinevere and Arthur together. Usually I'm all about her and Lancelot. Nope, not this time. I cannot wait for it to come on DVD. On a different note, I am officially obsessed with Ryan Kwanten from Summerland. All of my icons are of him. He's just so damn perfect. GUH! SOOOOO gorgeous. OK, sorry, I'm done now. :)

So, I didnt have some big shindig or anything but yesterday was pretty much perfect. We had ice cream cake at about noon because my dad had to leave to go work up in Minnesota (he started with a new company that is based up there and since they arent starting to work in WDM for a few weeks, he has to get work somehow so he goes up to Minn for the week, comes back for the weekend and then leaves again. I think this is going to go on for at least a few weeks). Then, we pretty much just chilled until it was time to go to dinner. We were going to go to Osceolas "fancy" restaraunt called Crossroads but we found out that they were closed Sunday nights, so instead I decided to go and eat at Pizza Hut, c'mon its friggin pizza baby!!! And then we rented some movies. It was my kind of thing. Be with my family and of course movies :) So, all in all, it was a good day. 
Then, today we went up to WDM and I got my own cell phone plan and new phone. I'm happy. I had to put a $400 down payment on it because I have no credit, plus the 100 some odd dollars for my phone + the plan, so it came out to like $537 and I had $535 in cash with me. But once I have this plan and pay on time for a full year I get the 400 back. My mom only thought that I had maybe 100 bucks because I now have a checking account and she thought all my money was in there. So when she found out that I had all that money she was like hell, go for it!! So I did. :)
Heres what it looks like http://i8.ebayimg.com/02/i/02/20/54/4c_1_b.JPG
Welcome all!!!! Ok, the only person that reads my journal is Jasmine so... Welcome Jasmine!!!!!! This is my new journal :) "Based" off of one of my new fave bands The Calling.
